10:31.832 --> 10:34.933
Look... Oh, you warmed
my buns.

10:34.935 --> 10:35.333
Yes.

10:35.335 --> 10:36.501
I don't know
if I can handle
all this meat.

10:36.503 --> 10:39.337
(UNDER BREATH) Is she
kidding me with this?
(UNDER BREATH) Just go.

10:39.339 --> 10:42.207
ADULT ADAM:
<i>No one was really</i>
<i>enjoying themselves...</i>

10:42.209 --> 10:45.310
<i>Except for Barry.</i>
<i>(THUNDER RUMBLING)</i>

10:46.679 --> 10:47.712
Hello, sister.

10:47.714 --> 10:49.581
Perfect day for
a barbecue, isn't it?

10:49.583 --> 10:52.384
No, weirdo.
It's pouring outside.

10:52.386 --> 10:53.018
Oh, I'm sorry.

10:53.020 --> 10:55.453
I meant,
it's a perfect day
for revenge.

10:55.455 --> 10:56.287
(BUTTON CLICKS)

10:56.289 --> 10:57.822
ERICA: (ON TAPE)
<i>Drew Kremp is so delicious.</i>

10:57.824 --> 11:01.026
<i>I want to dunk him</i>
<i>in a glass of milk</i>
<i>and eat him up.</i>

11:01.028 --> 11:02.761
(RECORDING STOPS)
What the hell?

11:02.763 --> 11:04.195
You recorded
my private phone call?

11:04.197 --> 11:07.499
Funny... How I just
happened to pick up
when you were on the phone.

11:07.501 --> 11:10.001
Should I play the rest
for the guests
we're entertaining?

11:10.003 --> 11:11.236
(LOWERED VOICE)
Okay, you win.

11:11.238 --> 11:12.570
You can use the phone
whenever you want, okay?

11:12.572 --> 11:14.372
Just please don't play it,
I'm begging you.

11:14.374 --> 11:17.509
Kind of like
how I begged you
not to tell dad, huh?

11:17.511 --> 11:19.911
Perchance, can you remind me
how that turned out?

11:19.913 --> 11:22.747
Will you stop
talking like that and
just give me the damn tape?

11:22.749 --> 11:23.715
No.
Just give it...

11:23.717 --> 11:24.883
Not giving it to you.
Stop it!

11:24.885 --> 11:26.551
(STRAINED VOICE)
You're embarrassing yourself.

11:26.553 --> 11:27.752
Give it...
Stop!

11:27.754 --> 11:29.054
Oh, my God! Stop!
(TAPE RECORDER THUDS)

11:29.056 --> 11:31.690
ERICA: ( ON TAPE)
<i>I mean, doesn't</i>
<i>Erica Kremp sound perfect?</i>

11:31.692 --> 11:32.957
<i>When we get married,</i>
<i>we're gonna ski</i>

11:32.959 --> 11:36.861
<i>and speak French</i>
<i>all day and have</i>
<i>super blonde kids.</i>

11:37.163 --> 11:38.096
Whoa.

11:38.098 --> 11:39.064
Oh, dear.

11:39.066 --> 11:41.566
That.was not the plan.

11:41.568 --> 11:42.634
What was the plan?

11:42.636 --> 11:45.437
(SHOUTING)
What was the plan?
Aah!

11:45.439 --> 11:46.438
Kids, enough!
BARRY: Ow! Ow!

11:46.440 --> 11:48.339
This is so out of
character for them.
ERICA: Stop moving.

11:48.341 --> 11:49.574
ERICA: Let me punch you!
BARRY: Get off me!

11:49.576 --> 11:52.343
Kids, I told you
not to punch each other
in the privates.

11:52.345 --> 11:54.212
No phone for
either of you.
Ow, ow, ow!

11:54.214 --> 11:57.182
ERICA: Stop moving!
(BARRY GRUNTING)

11:57.184 --> 11:58.049
ERICA: Eat it!

11:58.051 --> 12:00.285
Murray, wake
the (BLEEP) up!

12:00.287 --> 12:02.253
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

12:02.955 --> 12:03.488
(GASPS)

12:03.490 --> 12:04.989
Well, you know, it's...
It's getting late.

12:04.991 --> 12:06.257
We should probably
head out.

12:06.259 --> 12:08.026
Okay. Bye-bye now.
Good times.

12:08.028 --> 12:10.495
ADULT ADAM:
<i>A week went by,</i>
<i>and I hadn't seen Chad.</i>

12:10.497 --> 12:14.199
<i>Thankfully, Pops was always</i>
<i>there when I needed him.</i>

12:14.201 --> 12:16.367
Okay, and we're rolling.

12:16.369 --> 12:17.836
Action!

12:19.271 --> 12:20.472
What's my first line?

12:20.474 --> 12:21.840
Oh, come on, seriously?

12:21.842 --> 12:22.774
You got fruit punch
on your suit?

12:22.776 --> 12:26.978
Oh, it's okay. I...
I've given the character
a lot of thought.

12:26.980 --> 12:29.414
This robot loves
fruit punch.

12:29.416 --> 12:30.448
He's a messy robot.

12:30.450 --> 12:32.117
I told you,
you're not a robot.

12:32.119 --> 12:35.520
You're a program
living inside a digital
computer world.

12:35.522 --> 12:39.991
Or... Instead of him going
to a computer world,

12:39.993 --> 12:42.026
how about he goes
to a juice world?

12:42.028 --> 12:44.596
(ANGRILY)
There's no such thing
as a juice world!

12:44.598 --> 12:46.297
But computer worlds
are real?

12:46.299 --> 12:47.031
(SIGHS) Just go.

12:47.033 --> 12:49.234
I don't know
why a robot
can't like juice.

12:49.236 --> 12:51.035
Where's Chad today?

12:51.037 --> 12:55.073
Uh, I... I don't think
he's available.

12:55.075 --> 12:55.740
What do you mean?

12:55.742 --> 13:00.078
His mom just said
we can't play together
for a while.

13:00.080 --> 13:01.045
What?

13:01.047 --> 13:01.913
The nerve of that woman.

13:01.915 --> 13:03.047
I'm marching over there
right now

13:03.049 --> 13:04.449
and giving her
a piece of my mind.

13:04.451 --> 13:08.019
No! Wait! your mind
is the part that
scares her the most.

13:08.021 --> 13:10.255
Promise me you won't
go over there.

13:10.257 --> 13:13.124
Please. You'll just
make it worse.

13:13.126 --> 13:14.826
All right, lovebug.

13:14.828 --> 13:16.060
I won't go over there,
I promise.

13:16.062 --> 13:19.197
ADULT ADAM:
<i>My mom was a woman</i>
<i>of her word.</i>

13:19.199 --> 13:21.099
<i>She didn't march</i>
<i>over there.</i>

13:21.101 --> 13:22.433
<i>Instead, she called.</i>
<i>(LINE RINGING)</i>

13:22.435 --> 13:25.637
VIRGINIA: (OVER VOICEMAIL)
<i>Hello. You've reached</i>
<i>the Kremps.</i>

13:25.639 --> 13:29.174
<i>Please leave a message</i>
<i>and have a wonderful day.</i>

13:29.176 --> 13:29.607
(BEEPING)

13:29.609 --> 13:32.911
Virginia, it's
Beverly Goldberg.
Pick up.

13:32.913 --> 13:35.513
Oh, please, I see you
lurking behind the curtain

13:35.515 --> 13:37.382
like a weirdo
in your own home.

13:37.384 --> 13:38.483
Would you pick up
the phone already?

13:38.485 --> 13:40.051
(RECEIVER CLATTERS)
So sorry, I was just
in the shower.

13:40.053 --> 13:43.087
<i>Cut the crap and tell me</i>
<i>why Adam can't play</i>
<i>with Chad.</i>

13:43.089 --> 13:48.159
I'm sorry.
Look, I just hink that
we have different styles...

13:48.161 --> 13:50.361
Different ways of speaking

13:50.363 --> 13:51.129
in front of our children,

13:51.131 --> 13:57.569
and just generally
different ways of
being in the world.

13:57.571 --> 13:58.336
Fine.

13:58.338 --> 14:00.438
If Chad can't play
with Adam,

14:00.440 --> 14:02.473
Adam can't play with Chad.

14:02.475 --> 14:04.442
And I could give a hoot
whether or not you like me

14:04.444 --> 14:09.214
because I have buttloads
of friends, okay?

14:09.415 --> 14:10.515
Buttloads.

14:10.517 --> 14:13.117
(SLAMS DOWN RECEIVER)
(GASPS)

14:13.819 --> 14:17.322
I... kept my promise.

14:17.489 --> 14:19.591
I didn't go over there.

14:19.593 --> 14:21.459
(RAPID FOOTSTEPS DEPART)
ADULT ADAM:
<i>And just like that,</i>

14:21.461 --> 14:24.596
<i>my mom had hung up</i>
<i>on my friendship</i>
<i>with Chad.</i>

14:24.598 --> 14:27.632
<i>But we weren't</i>
<i>the only ones getting</i>
<i>our lines crossed.</i>

14:27.634 --> 14:30.635
<i>My brother and sister's</i>
<i>battle over the phone</i>

14:30.637 --> 14:32.503
<i>had stretched on</i>
<i>another day.</i>

14:32.505 --> 14:35.373
<i>But what Barry would soon</i>
<i>realize was the fight</i>

14:35.375 --> 14:38.710
<i>was about to be</i>
<i>taken outside.</i>

14:38.712 --> 14:41.713
I'm serious, Lainey.
Drew Kremp
heard everything.

14:41.715 --> 14:45.884
I'm thinking of
quitting school
and skipping town.

14:45.886 --> 14:47.285
Busted! You are so busted,

14:47.287 --> 14:49.554
and I'm telling,
and Barry wins.

14:49.556 --> 14:51.522
Mom and dad said
we couldn't use the phone

14:51.524 --> 14:52.156
in the house.

14:52.158 --> 14:55.093
Technically...
I'm outside the house.

14:55.095 --> 14:56.127
That's very intelligent.

14:56.129 --> 14:57.929
Give it to me!
I gotta make a call!

14:57.931 --> 14:59.330
No way!
It was my idea!

14:59.332 --> 15:00.732
Just give it to me!
Stop!

15:00.734 --> 15:03.101
Lainey, hold on!

15:03.769 --> 15:04.302
(BELL DINGS)

15:04.304 --> 15:07.105
(STRAINED VOICE)
Give it...to me.

15:07.107 --> 15:08.973
(WHOOSHES)

15:09.375 --> 15:11.109
(GRUNTS)

15:12.578 --> 15:13.244
You broke it!

15:13.246 --> 15:15.513
Maybe you should call
9-7-6-new-phone.

15:15.515 --> 15:17.382
Maybe you should call...

15:17.384 --> 15:18.683
Shut up!

15:18.685 --> 15:19.951
(GASPS)

15:19.953 --> 15:21.786
Are you kidding me?

15:21.788 --> 15:23.454
I stand by what I did.

15:23.456 --> 15:24.923
God!

15:24.925 --> 15:26.324
Why are we like this?

15:26.326 --> 15:28.159
'Cause we're a family.

15:28.161 --> 15:28.927
That's what a family does.

15:28.929 --> 15:32.463
All we ever do is fight,
and it's exhausting.

15:33.132 --> 15:33.865
Wait.

15:33.867 --> 15:37.001
You're not gonna
throw mud back in my face?

15:37.236 --> 15:39.137
What do I do?

15:39.972 --> 15:42.040
Tell me, what do I do?

15:44.410 --> 15:47.478
ADULT ADAM:
<i>For the next week,</i>
<i>my mom and Virginia Kremp</i>

15:47.480 --> 15:48.246
<i>avoided each other.</i>

15:48.248 --> 15:52.717
<i>But in a small town,</i>
<i>you can only avoid</i>
<i>someone for so long.</i>

15:52.719 --> 15:57.288
I knew something
was wrong because when
I bit into the eclair,

15:57.290 --> 15:58.923
it tasted like sour cream
and pickles.

15:58.925 --> 16:02.126
If they went bad,
they went bad
on your watch.

16:02.128 --> 16:03.328
I can see
why you would think that.

16:03.330 --> 16:07.131
And normally I would never...
Ever, ever make a fuss.

16:07.133 --> 16:09.968
But I did purchase these
less than 24 hours ago,

16:09.970 --> 16:11.536
and I still have the receipt.

16:11.538 --> 16:13.204
I'm not takin' these back!

16:13.206 --> 16:13.805
Are you kidding me?

16:13.807 --> 16:16.841
ADULT ADAM:
<i>My mom may have been able</i>
<i>to give up on Virginia,</i>

16:16.843 --> 16:20.078
<i>but she couldn't give up</i>
<i>on who she was.</i>

16:20.080 --> 16:20.712
Mrs. Goldberg,

16:20.714 --> 16:22.213
I... I didn't know
you two knew each other.

16:22.215 --> 16:23.581
Damn right we do.
We're neighbors.

16:23.583 --> 16:27.251
Now... Go back
and get her
some fresh eclairs.

16:27.253 --> 16:28.720
Or would you
like a repeat...

16:28.722 --> 16:32.090
(LOUDLY)
...of the birthday
cake fiasco?

16:32.092 --> 16:34.759
Who writes
"Sorry for your loss"

16:34.761 --> 16:36.127
on a 10-year-old's
birthday cake?

16:36.129 --> 16:39.163
It was a mistake,
and Victor was let go.
Yeah.

16:39.165 --> 16:41.833
Well, that was a dark day
for this store.

16:41.835 --> 16:44.535
But it could get
a lot darker.

16:44.537 --> 16:45.603
I'll take care of it.

16:45.605 --> 16:48.673
Sorry, ma'am.
I'll fix you right up.

16:49.141 --> 16:51.609
(SIGHS)

16:51.977 --> 16:54.879
I know I just made
a big, loud scene.

16:56.215 --> 16:58.683
It's just what I do.

17:01.887 --> 17:04.389
Knock, knock. Honey?

17:04.456 --> 17:05.623
Are you in there?

17:05.625 --> 17:08.559
ADAM: Go away.
I don't wanna talk to you.

17:09.962 --> 17:13.031
You're right.
I should give you
some space.

17:15.034 --> 17:18.369
At least close the door,
and don't turn on
the lights.

17:18.371 --> 17:20.638
Darkness is my only friend.

17:23.575 --> 17:25.143
(DOOR CLOSING)

17:25.644 --> 17:27.111
BEVERLY:
Adam, I am so sorry.

17:27.113 --> 17:29.347
ADAM: You should be sorry!
Look at me!

17:29.349 --> 17:31.682
I'm in a glow-in-the-dark
unitard!

17:31.684 --> 17:34.852
(SIGHS) And Chad
was the only friend
that got me...

17:34.854 --> 17:36.187
Who got  <i>this!</i>

17:36.189 --> 17:38.189
And you just had to
ruin it...

17:38.191 --> 17:42.827
Just because one person
in this world
didn't like you.

17:43.896 --> 17:44.896
(SWITCH CLICKS)

17:44.898 --> 17:48.933
Sweetie, you're the one
that matters.

17:49.301 --> 17:50.435
I'd rather have nobody
like me

17:50.437 --> 17:53.938
than have you be
mad at me forever.

17:57.042 --> 18:00.678
Not forever, just for
about a month and a half.

18:00.680 --> 18:02.413
Well...

18:02.415 --> 18:04.882
Let's see if I can
shorten that up
just a bit.

18:04.884 --> 18:07.585
(STARSHIP'S  <i>NOTHING'S GONNA</i>
<i>STOP US NOW</i> PLAYING)

18:07.587 --> 18:09.087
Yo.

18:10.489 --> 18:11.422
Yo.

18:11.424 --> 18:13.091
Whatcha doin'?

18:13.093 --> 18:14.258
Nothing.

18:14.260 --> 18:15.760
Want to finish our movie?

18:15.762 --> 18:16.561
Yeah. Do you?

18:16.563 --> 18:18.996
(CHUCKLES) Hell, yeah.
Chad, "h" word.

18:18.998 --> 18:20.565
Sorry.

18:23.902 --> 18:25.369
Cool.

18:26.371 --> 18:29.207
What the hell's
the "h" word?

18:29.775 --> 18:32.410
So I was thinking
tomorrow we could
go for a power walk.

18:32.412 --> 18:36.114
And then you could
come over and we could
split an eclair.

18:36.116 --> 18:38.149
Or I could come over
right now,

18:38.151 --> 18:40.151
and we could each have
our  <i>own</i> eclair.

18:40.153 --> 18:42.553
Mmm, Beverly Goldberg,
you are bad.
(CHUCKLES)

18:42.555 --> 18:45.790
I am bad.
I am the worst.
(LAUGHS)

18:45.792 --> 18:47.992
Let's do it.
(WHISPERS) Let's do it.

18:47.994 --> 18:48.426
Okay.

18:48.428 --> 18:50.361
ADULT ADAM:
<i>And just like that,</i>
<i>the one person out there</i>

18:50.363 --> 18:52.663
<i>who didn't like my mom</i>
<i>became her best friend.</i>

18:52.665 --> 18:57.135
<i>Even my dad,</i>
<i>who prided himself</i>
<i>on having no friends,</i>

18:57.137 --> 19:01.038
<i>started to come around</i>
<i>to the idea.</i>

19:01.040 --> 19:03.341
(KEYS JANGLE)
Yo.

19:03.343 --> 19:04.542
Yo.

19:04.544 --> 19:05.643
Whatcha doin'?

19:05.645 --> 19:07.912
Uh, nothin'.
Hey, uh...

19:07.914 --> 19:10.581
I don't know if you're
interested, but, um...

19:10.583 --> 19:13.050
I got Eagles
season tickets...

19:13.052 --> 19:15.853
50 yard line.
(CHUCKLES)

19:15.855 --> 19:16.487
You around Sunday?

19:16.489 --> 19:19.690
<i>♪ And we can build</i>
<i>this thing together ♪</i>

19:19.692 --> 19:21.025
Yeah!

19:21.027 --> 19:22.360
ADULT ADAM:
<i>Watching the Kremp kids</i>
<i>get along</i>

19:22.362 --> 19:26.430
<i>inspired Barry and Erica</i>
<i>to try something</i>
<i>new and crazy..</i> .

19:26.432 --> 19:28.399
<i>Look out for each other.</i>

19:28.401 --> 19:29.100
BARRY: Hey, Chad.

19:29.102 --> 19:32.036
You want to bet
I can't climb the tree
in your yard?

19:32.038 --> 19:33.337
Yeah!

19:33.339 --> 19:35.406
<i>♪ Nothing's gonna stop us</i>

19:35.408 --> 19:38.476
<i>♪ Nothing's gonna stop us</i>

19:38.478 --> 19:39.710
<i>♪ Now. Whoa, oh</i>

19:39.712 --> 19:41.546
ADULT ADAM:
<i>we learned a lot</i>
<i>from each other.</i>

19:41.548 --> 19:42.513
<i>We taught them</i>
<i>it was okay</i>

19:42.515 --> 19:44.382
<i>to raise your voice</i>
<i>now and then.</i>

19:44.384 --> 19:45.783
I asked for paper-thin.

19:45.785 --> 19:46.784
You gave me slices...

19:46.786 --> 19:49.954
Thick as my thumb...
Not acceptable.

19:49.956 --> 19:52.356
<i>♪ I will stay here</i>
<i>with you ♪</i>

19:52.358 --> 19:55.059
ADULT ADAM:
<i>While they learned how to be</i>
<i>more like the Goldbergs,</i>

19:55.061 --> 19:58.429
<i>we learned to be</i>
<i>a little more</i>
<i>like the Kremps.</i>

19:58.431 --> 19:59.764
Erica, telephone.

19:59.766 --> 20:02.333
ERICA:  <i>What?</i>
<i>Push the button, mom.</i>

20:02.335 --> 20:03.901
<i>Uh... It's not hard.</i>
<i>Erica...</i>

20:03.903 --> 20:06.604
<i>How many times</i>
<i>do I have to show you</i>
<i>how this works.</i>

20:06.606 --> 20:08.139
How does this
stupid thing work?

20:08.141 --> 20:09.740
Erica, telephone...
<i>Talk into the box!</i>

20:09.742 --> 20:11.409
(SHOUTING)
Erica! Telephone!
Hello?

20:11.411 --> 20:13.911
Pick up the damn phone!
<i>What's the matter</i>
<i>with you? Mom?</i>

20:13.913 --> 20:16.714
ADULT ADAM:
<i>Yep, we were different</i>
<i>than the Kremps...</i>

20:16.716 --> 20:18.816
<i>Not better, not worse..</i> .

20:18.818 --> 20:20.151
<i>Just... Different.</i>

20:20.153 --> 20:21.619
<i>Told you I could</i>
<i>do it again.</i>

20:21.621 --> 20:22.620
<i>You're so stupid</i>
<i>for doubting me.</i>

20:22.622 --> 20:27.959
ADULT ADAM: (SIGHS)
<i>Oh, though Barry</i>
<i>didn't help our case.</i>

20:28.594 --> 20:31.762
Okay, folks.
Today we're re-enacting

20:31.764 --> 20:33.698
some "Empire strikes back."

20:33.700 --> 20:34.532
Are you ready?

20:34.534 --> 20:36.000
Dude, are you sure
about this?

20:36.002 --> 20:38.970
(CHUCKLES)
Oh, I'm sure.
Keep it rolling.

20:39.371 --> 20:41.305
(CLATTERING)

20:43.642 --> 20:46.043
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

20:47.546 --> 20:48.813
What's goin' on?

20:48.815 --> 20:49.480
(LAUGHS)

20:49.482 --> 20:52.350
Oh, why do you always
do this crap?

20:52.851 --> 20:53.618
I'm your father!

20:53.620 --> 20:56.621
(VOICE BREAKING)
No, that's not true.

20:56.623 --> 20:57.355
That's impossible!

20:57.357 --> 20:59.590
What do you mean
"impossible"?
(MASK CLATTERS)

20:59.592 --> 21:01.993
Get the hell outta here!
Run!

21:01.995 --> 21:03.794
(BOTH LAUGHING)
